Title: VERSUNI 2025 TEMPLATE Handsticks Dry
Description:
Please read the instructions below carefully before you start this task. This is so you are fully prepared before you begin this task. If you’re asked any questions, please refer them to UKSupport@roamler.com. 

This is a Mystery task, but you will need to speak to the instore staff as a customer!

Aim of the task
In this check you will be looking for household appliances in the category Handsticks Dry.

You will:

*   Search for the categorie in store
*   Answer some questions about brand-visibility and brand-availability
*   Take pictures of the products of the category
*   Strike up a conversation - Talk to a member of staff and ask for a recommendation for a product of the category.

Make sure you do not blow your cover on this task! Remain a mystery guest at all times. 

Ensure that you check the opening times for the location you are visiting so that you do not visit when they are closed. 

Use the address in the task. The pin is there as a guide only. Only visit during opening hours. If you visit during closing hours, your task will not be accepted.

Turned away or closed you will be paid a maximum of £2 on the first instance of this happening.

ReviewNotes:
Please be very carful that really the right products are captured!

Locations closed/Sent away: If store is closed/sent away, hidden, +1 taskgroup, 2euro

Questions.Text:
Notes: 
Although you can complete different tasks at each store  - its very important that you are able to maintain your cover as a Mystery Shopper! 

Tips!:
Have a story ready about why you are interested in so many different types of products! 

Maybe you have just bought a new home and are looking to set it up with new appliances. 

It could be you are getting married - and are looking for things to put on your wedding gift list!

Questions.Text:
You are going to capture shelves per bay. Please follow those rules while taking the pictures:

*   Bays are the sections in which the fixture is divided. A bay is limited by a small gap in the shelves. See photos below, every photo is one bay.
*   Photos right in front of the shelf
*   Take vertical photos per bay.
*   Make sure the bay is captured from top to bottom. No missing or half shelves!
*   As close as possible while capturing the full shelf
*   Keep same distance
*   Focus the photo on one bay
*   Make sure every photo has a bit of overlap (10-30%) with the adjacent bays
*   Make sure the photos are sharp, also for the products on the top and bottom shelves
*   Avoid overexposed photos or photos which are too dark. Pay attention to the top and bottom shelves also!
*   Start taking the pictures from the left side of the section and move towards the right side. In case that there are products of the category on both sides of the shelf once you are done with the first side go to the other side of the aisle and start from the left side again.

See examples of bay photos below.
